<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
The syntype series was lost during a plane crash when the material loaned to B. H. Lamoral was sent back to Hamburg (label in jar from H. Dastych: &quot;B. H. Lamoral 18.XI.1974; Das ganze Material ist verloren, 1975. Das Flugzeug ist 
<normalizedToken originalValue="abgestürzt”">abgestuerzt&quot;</normalizedToken>
). Lamoral and Reynders (1975: 563) established 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Opisthophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opisthophthalmus werneri" order="Scorpiones" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="werneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Opisthophthalmus werneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. pilosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Werner, 1936 wich is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. pilosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. L. Koch, 1838. 
<bibRefCitation author="Prendini, L" journalOrPublisher="African Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" pagination="17 - 48" refId="B144" refString="Prendini, L, 2001. A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae). African Entomology 9: 17 - 48" title="A review of synonyms and subspecies in the genus Opistophthalmus C. L. Koch (Scorpiones: Scorpionidae)." volume="9" year="2001">Prendini (2001</bibRefCitation>
: see p.24 for details) later demonstrated that 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. werneri" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="werneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">O. werneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Opisthophthalmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opisthophthalmus flavescens" order="Scorpiones" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Opisthophthalmus flavescens</emphasis>
